<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12205i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12205i">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12205i"> 205(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> cette petite petite</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Les babouins lui dirent: &ldquo;Nous ne d&eacute;sirons pas autre chose que ton sang; nous voudrions que tu le verses dans une petite gourde.&rdquo; L&apos;&eacute;l&eacute;phant dit: &ldquo;<mark>Cette petite petite!</mark> venez et saignez-moi.&rdquo; <br>Note 1. Allusion &agrave; la coutume qu&apos;ont les Massa&iuml;, tr&egrave;s friands de sang chaud, de pratiquer des saign&eacute;es sur leurs b&oelig;ufs, dont ils recueillent le sang dans des gourdes pour le boire aussit&ocirc;t apr&egrave;s. <br><font color="green">[The baboons told him: &ldquo;We don&apos;t want anything but your blood, we would like you to pour it in this little gourd&rdquo;. The elephant replied: &ldquo;<mark>This little little!</mark> Come and let my blood.&rdquo; <br>Note 1. Alludes to the custom of the Massai, who very much like to drink warm blood, to bleed their cattle, the blood of which the catch in gourds to drink it immediately.]</font> <small> Maurice Delafosse, <a name="LNEG" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#LNEG"><cite title="source">L'&acirc;me n&egrave;gre</cite></a> (1922) 54</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c12202i" href="c12all.htm#c12202i">VI.C.12:202(i)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
